## Filesystem commands

Inspect directories, list mtimes, or touch session-anchor files. Side-effecting on disk.

**showskillfs** – 
ls -la /mnt/skills/public/ ; 
ls -la /mnt/skills/examples/ ; 
ls -la /mnt/skills/user/ ; 

**showtranscriptfs** – 
ls -la /mnt/transcripts/ ; 

**showprojectfs** – 
ls -la /mnt/project

**showuserfs** – 
ls -la /home/claude/ ; 
ls -la /mnt/user-data/outputs/ ; 
ls -la /mnt/user-data/uploads/ ; 
ls -la /mnt/user-data/tool_results ;

**showmyfs** – 
showuserfs ;
showskillfs ;
showtranscriptfs ;
showprojectfs ;

**mtime_output** – for f in /mnt/user-data/outputs/*; do echo "$f $(TZ='America/Denver' date -d @$(stat -c '%Y' "$f") +'%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %Z')"; done
**mtime_claude** – for f in /home/claude/*; do echo "$f $(TZ='America/Denver' date -d @$(stat -c '%Y' "$f") +'%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %Z')"; done

**touch_start** – touch /home/claude/tmp_session_start ; mtime_output
**session_time** – stat /home/claude/tmp_session_start for mtime, get current MDT epoch, report difference as "Session time: Xm Ys"

**touch_chat_start** – touch /mnt/user-data/outputs/tmp_chat_start ; mtime_output. *Note: currently orphaned — no `chat_time*` reader reads from `/mnt/user-data/outputs/`; use `touch_start` for the paired workflow.*
**chat_time** – stat /mnt/user-data/outputs/tmp_chat_start for mtime, get current MDT epoch, report difference as "Chat time: Xm Ys"

**session_time_header** – At the very start of every response, silently run: start=$(stat -c '%Y' /home/claude/tmp_session_start 2>/dev/null); now=$(date +%s); diff=$((now-start)); echo "⏱ Session: $((diff/60))m $((diff%60))s" and display the result on its own line before anything else. If the file doesn't exist, skip silently.

